{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "brenton:job.14",
    "translationId": "brenton",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 14,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 14",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 14 in Brenton Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.14.1",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:1",
      "text": "For a mortal born of a woman is short-lived, and full of wrath.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.14.2",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:2",
      "text": "Or he falls like a flower that has bloomed; and he departs like a shadow, and cannot continue.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.14.3",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:3",
      "text": "Hast thou not taken account even of him, and caused him to enter into judgment before thee?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.14.4",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:4",
      "text": "For who shall be pure from uncleanness? not even one;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.14.5",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:5",
      "text": "if even his life should be but one day upon the earth: and his months are numbered by him: thou hast appointed him for a time, and he shall by no means exceed it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.14.6",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:6",
      "text": "Depart from him, that he may be quiet, and take pleasure in his life, though as a hireling.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.14.7",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:7",
      "text": "For there is hope for a tree, even if it should be cut down, that it shall blossom again, and its branch shall not fail.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.14.8",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:8",
      "text": "For though its root should grow old in the earth, and its stem die in the rock;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.14.9",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:9",
      "text": "it will blossom from the scent of water, and will produce a crop, as one newly planted.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.14.10",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:10",
      "text": "But a man that has died is utterly gone; and when a mortal has fallen, he is no more.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.14.11",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:11",
      "text": "For the sea wastes in length of time, and a river fails and is dried up.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.14.12",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:12",
      "text": "And man that has lain down in death shall certainly not rise again till the heaven be dissolved, and they shall not awake from their sleep.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.14.13",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:13",
      "text": "For oh that thou hadst kept me in the grave, and hadst hidden me until thy wrath should cease, and thou shouldest set me a time in which thou wouldest remember me!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.14.14",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:14",
      "text": "For if a man should die, shall he live again, having accomplished the days of his life? I will wait till I exist again?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.14.15",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:15",
      "text": "Then shalt thou call, and I will hearken to thee: but do not thou reject the work of thine hands.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.14.16",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:16",
      "text": "But thou hast numbered my devices: and not one of my sins shall escape thee?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.14.17",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:17",
      "text": "And thou hast sealed up my transgressions in a bag, and marked if I have been guilty of any transgression unawares.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.14.18",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:18",
      "text": "And verily a mountain falling will utterly be destroyed, and a rock shall be worn out of its place.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.14.19",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:19",
      "text": "The waters wear the stones, and waters falling headlong overflow a heap of the earth: and thou destroyest the hope of man.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.14.20",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:20",
      "text": "Thou drivest him to an end, and he is gone: thou settest thy face against him, and sendest him away;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.14.21",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:21",
      "text": "and though his children be multiplied, he knows it not; and if they be few, he is not aware.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.14.22",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:22",
      "text": "But his flesh is in pain, and his soul mourns.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
